<h2><span><span style="color: blue">Note: If you're going to introduce yourself here, please scroll down and click &quot;New Post&quot; and NOT &quot;reply&quot;, otherwise your comment will nest incorrectly!</span></span></h2>
<p>Hello, readers and reviewers of the Foundation Universe!</p>
<h3><span>This month's random question is: what sound always puts you in a good mood?</span></h3>
<p>Let's start off with some things to take a look at to enhance your reading, now that you're a site member:</p>
<ul>
<li>If you have any <strong>questions about the Foundation'verse</strong> and its various individuals and groups of interest, head over to the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-88827/foundation-universe">Foundation Universe forum</a> to talk about the various aspects of living/working/being in constant fear of a world where anomalies are real.</li>
<li>Did you know our site has a <strong>night mode</strong> version? If you're interested in that (and a few other neat things!), check out our <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/usertools">Usertools</a> page.</li>
<li>Want to <strong>leave a comment</strong> or read others' thoughts on something you've read recently? Scroll down to the bottom of that page you read, click the &quot;Discuss&quot; link, and take a look at the comments others have posted!</li>
</ul>
<p>For those looking to put your knowledge of the SCP-verse to work and contribute to the site by helping develop works-in-progress, head on over to the Writing Help forums!</p>
<ul>
<li><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-9804362/so-you-want-to-be-a-concept-reviewer">So you want to be a concept reviewer?</a></strong></li>
<li><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-9804215/so-you-want-to-be-a-draft-reviewer">So you want to be a draft reviewer?</a></strong></li>
<li>And of course, remember the <a href="/criticism-policy">Criticism Policy</a>!</li>
</ul>
<p>If you're not sure what to talk about here, you can take a look at our <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-985304/how-to-write-an-intro-or-welcome">How to Write an Intro/Welcome</a> thread for ideas.</p>
<p>Go ahead and respond to other new members if you find that your interests overlap, and definitely ask for reading suggestions if there's a particular kind of SCP article or tale you enjoy reading. If you're looking to get started as a critiquer, feel free to mention the kind of material you particularly want to see more of on the wiki! You might even see some of our authors drop by here from time to time, if you mention you liked their work! :)</p>
<p>Welcome to the site!</p>

